accessibility.text: PSRs arise out out of a fundamental evolutionary deficiency of the human brain and its inability to keep pace in a increasingly mediated world* (Kanazawa, 2002, p.168)
we have no way to make sense of characters other than to treat it like a social relationship
*although this may underestimate human intelligence, i suspect it bears some reflection of psychological processes of understanding character (i.e. we understand through experience)
